'''Pool Academy''' is a [[Mixed-sex education|coeducational]] [[secondary school]] with [[Academy (English school)|academy status]], located in [[Pool, Cornwall|Pool]] in the [[English county]] of [[Cornwall]].<ref>http://www.poolacademy.co.uk/</ref>

The school was previously known as Pool Comprehensive School before gaining specialist status when it was renamed Poole [[Business and Enterprise College]]. The school converted to academy status on 1 April 2011 and was renamed Pool Academy. 

Pool Academy offers [[General Certificate of Secondary Education|GCSEs]] and [[Cambridge Nationals]] as programmes of study for pupils. The school is also the [[Home (sports)|home ground]] of [[Duchy Hockey Club]].<ref>http://www.duchyhockeyclub.com/node/10</ref>

